The closest analogue of NIR is the RUSALKA instrument (Russian acronym for Manual Spectral Analyzer of the Atmosphere Constituents), flown on the International Space Station (ISS) in 2009–2012 (Korablev et al. 2011). RUSALKA covered the spectral range of 0.7–1.65 μm with a resolving power of λ/Δλ≈20,000\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
