The spectral range of the instrument (0.73–1.6 μm) corresponds to the echelle diffraction orders from 48 through 105. The spectral resolution is limited by the slit width and aberrations of the off-axis parabolic collimator. Following the sampling theorem (2 pixels per resolution element) the resolving power of an aberration-free spectrometer reaches R≈27,500\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
