Similar to the ACS-NIR the echelle-spectrometer of MIR employs the autocollimation Littrow scheme. Two conditions are needed to achieve a high spectral resolution: firstly, the echelle grating must be large enough and have a high linear dispersion. The diffraction-limited resolving power is given by 
