After the Mars orbit insertion on 19 October 2016 the Mars Capture Orbit (MCO) campaign of observations was carried out in November 2016. On the top of the checks done during the MCC, this campaign allowed for first Mars observations from near the pericenter of two highly elliptical orbits (380×66,000km\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
