Measurements of solar spectrum were carried out in laboratory and in flight in April, June, and November 2016 (Fig. 28). The maximum SNR appears to be quite low ∼170 in its maximum at 4000 cm−1 (for a measurement time of 1.8 s, see Table 4). In the following we use a conservative SNR=50\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
